ssociated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes Despenser was born about 1390, in Nettlestead, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Sir John Edward Watkins IV. She died about 1416, in Creeksea, Essex, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 28."},"et":{"about 1390–about 1416":"umbes 1390–umbes 1416","1395–1478":"1395–1478","1410–1478":"1410–1478","1390–1416":"1390–1416","about 1390":"umbes 1390","1478":"1478","1410":"1410","about 1416":"umbes 1416","1395":"1395","1390":"1390","1416":"1416","Nettlestead, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Nettlestead, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Holwell, Dorset, England":"Holwell, Dorset, England","Creeksea, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Creeksea, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1390–about 1416":"noin 1390–noin 1416","1395–1478":"1395–1478","1410–1478":"1410–1478","1390–1416":"1390–1416","about 1390":"noin 1390","1478":"1478","1410":"1410","about 1416":"noin 1416","1395":"1395","1390":"1390","1416":"1416","Nettlestead, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Nettlestead, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Holwell, Dorset, England":"Holwell, Dorset, England","Creeksea, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Creeksea, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1390–about 1416":"environ 1390–environ 1416","1395–1478":"1395–1478","1410–1478":"1410–1478","1390–1416":"1390–1416","about 1390":"environ 1390","1478":"1478","1410":"1410","about 1416":"environ 1416","1395":"1395","1390":"1390","1416":"1416","Nettlestead, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Nettlestead, Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","